SIMPLE: squeegee
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Squeegee
<hw>Squee"gee</hw> <pr>(skw⟦emac⟧"j⟦esl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>Formerly, a small swab for drying a vessel's deck; now, a kind of
scraper having a blade or edge of rubber or of leather, -- used for
removing superfluous, water or other liquids, as from a vessel's deck
after washing, from window panes, photographer's plates, etc.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>squilgee</asp>,
<asp>squillagee</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squeegee</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Squeegee
<hw>Squee"gee</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Squeegeed</conjf> <pr>(skw⟦emac⟧"j⟦emac⟧d;
skw⟦emac⟧*j⟦emac⟧d")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Squeegeeing</conjf> <pr>(skw⟦emac⟧"j⟦emac⟧*⟦icr⟧ng;
skw⟦emac⟧*j⟦emac⟧"⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To smooth, clean, press,
or treat with a squeegee; to squilgee.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squeegee roller</ent>⟦br⟧
